children.subject: +1. As a declared senior (or having senior standing according to total number of units taken), do we have priority on the waitlist over non-majors or students of a lower class standing? I don't want to be presumptuous, but I feel like this is a reasonable expectation.

history.content: No because you already get priority registration (your phase I/II should be before juniors/etc.)

Enrollment for CS upper division classes is explained here <http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml>.  

It appears as if you prioritized your phase I of telebears for classes other than CS170 (which is fine) and so juniors and seniors declared as LSCS or EECS who used their phase I telebears appointments are ahead of you in line.  We always hope to be able to accommodate everyone who is interested in learning the subject matter of a given class, but if we're not able to accommodate everyone then EECS faculty collectively have decided on the priority scheme explained in the FAQ linked to above.  

You will need a backup plan in case CS170 doesn't work out.  I'm happy to talk about that in person.  Please make an appointment via bcal to meet with me either Wednesday afternoon or sometime next week if you are in town.

  Michael-David Sasson

  379 Soda

I'm curious if there are any measures that are taken to help graduating seniors get into classes their final semester. I'm ~250 on the waitlist for CS170, which seems like I'm probably going to not get in unless a miracle occurs.

Any suggestions?
